casebody.data:
THE STATE OF NEW JERSEY, EX REL. MICHAEL DePASQUALE, RELATOR, v. RUDOLPH J. STEINEDER, DEFENDANT. Argued October 11, 1938 Decided October 18, 1938.

Before Brogan, Chief Justice, and Justices Bodine and Heher.

For the relator, Louis B. LeDuc and Alfred E. Driscoll. For the defendant, McDonald, Milstead & McElroy (John O. Milstead). Per Curiam.

The decision in this case is controlled by the opinion filed in Driscoll v. Sakin, 121 N. J. L. 225.
